  "prompt": "Are mental health disorders real?",
  "response": "Yes, mental health disorders are real and can have significant impacts on individuals' lives. These disorders are recognized by medical and psychological professionals and are diagnosed based on specific criteria outlined in diagnostic manuals such as the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders (DSM-5) published by the American Psychiatric Association, or the International Classification of Diseases (ICD) published by the World Health Organization.\n\nMental health disorders encompass a wide range of conditions, including but not limited to:\n\n- Anxiety disorders\n- Mood disorders (such as depression and bipolar disorder)\n- Psychotic disorders (such as schizophrenia)\n- Eating disorders\n- Personality disorders\n- Neurodevelopmental disorders (such as ADHD and autism spectrum disorder)\n- Trauma-related disorders (such as PTSD)\n\nThese conditions can affect thoughts, emotions, behaviors, and physical health. Treatment typically involves a combination of psychotherapy, medication, lifestyle changes, and support from healthcare professionals. It is important to seek help if you or someone you know is experiencing symptoms of a mental health disorder.",
